 :tx/rationale "C9-COMPONENT-4: Contradiction detection across observations — surface disagreements between agents for deliberation. PROBLEM: Independent audit agents may disagree. My FULL_AUDIT rated C8 compliance of the PROJECT_ASSESSMENT as 'too generous' (it said 'MAINTAINED with minor tension' while the other 3 audits found systemic violations). The store has no mechanism to detect when observations contradict each other. Contradictions between independent agents are high-value signals — they identify areas of genuine uncertainty requiring deliberation. JUSTIFICATION: The coherence engine (coherence.rs) already implements Tier 1 (exact value conflicts) and Tier 2 (logical contradictions) for spec elements. Applying the same tiers to observations would surface: Tier 1 — two observations asserting different severity for the same finding. Tier 2 — one observation claiming a subsystem is SOUND while another claims UNSOUND. These contradictions should trigger the deliberation protocol (deliberation.rs), producing a Decision entity with rationale. SOLUTION: After clustering (C9-COMPONENT-1), within each cluster check for severity disagreements, conflicting soundness assessments, or contradictory recommendations. Flag these as Aleatory divergence (agent vs agent) and create deliberation-needed signals. VERIFICATION: The C8 compliance disagreement (PROJECT_ASSESSMENT vs other 3 audits) is detected and flagged. DEPENDENCIES: Requires C9-COMPONENT-1 (clustering). Uses existing coherence.rs and deliberation.rs. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/coherence.rs, concept.rs. EFFORT: 3h."
